Here is an example of terraform configuration code that deploys an AWS EC2 instance:
```
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = "3.29.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "aws" {
  region = "us-west-2"
}

resource "aws_instance" "example" {
  ami           = "ami-0ff8a91507f77f867"
  instance_type = "t2.micro"

  tags = {
    Name = "example-instance"
  }
}
```
Please note that this is a dummy example, you need to replace the `ami` and `region` with the real one for your desired use case. Also, you need to setup your AWS credentials in your local machine or in the environment variable. You may also need to configure security group and key pair.
